Marelize Barnard, Netwerk24Gerrit Scheepers with his parents Hardus and Dalene. (Facebook) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Houston - Detectives in Houston, Texas, are waiting for the results of post mortems on South African couple Hardus and Dalene Scheepers before they can say more about how they died,&nbsp;Netwerk24&nbsp;reported on Monday.The couple&rsquo;s bodies were found in their home in Houston on Thursday morning.According to a report on the local website, Click2Houston, an incident was reported to police at 09:00 (US time). &nbsp;A relative called police to say they hadn&rsquo;t heard from them in days. According to the report, there had been no sign of forced entry. The bodies were in separate rooms. &nbsp;Local resident Laura Gorten said it was a quiet neighbourhood and the police activity had come as a surprise.&nbsp;A homicide detective at the Houston police said on Sunday at 22:00 (SA time) that one of the bodies had signs of trauma.&nbsp;A message posted on their son Gerrit's Facebook page read: &ldquo;Ek en sussa is ontsaglik lief vir julle albei.&rdquo; (Sussa and I love you both dearly).The Scheepers apparently had two children. Their son was studying in the US.&ldquo;We don&rsquo;t know what happened,&rdquo; Frans Scheepers, a relative, was quoted as saying.&ldquo;I can&rsquo;t comment on Hardus and Daleen&rsquo;s death. I don&rsquo;t know if they were murdered and I don&rsquo;t have any more details,&rdquo; he said.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.